PN,43302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1776280294
OL,3,C'It ruins you': the impact of being
OL,4,Cindefinitely imprisoned
OL,6,FWest Country families have taken part
OL,7,Fin a Westminster protest against the
OL,8,Fcontinued incarceration of offenders
OL,9,Fgiven indeterminate sentences, known
OL,10,Fas Imprisonment for Public Protection
OL,11,F(IPP) sentences.
OL,13,FDespite being abolished in 2012, there
OL,14,Fare still thousands of prisoners
OL,15,Fserving open-ended sentences, which
OL,16,Fwere issued to people deemed dangerous
OL,17,Fbut whose offence did not merit a life
OL,18,Fsentence.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/15
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,434,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1776280294
OL,3,C'It ruins you': the impact of being
OL,4,Cindefinitely imprisoned
OL,6,FThe Ministry of Justice says it is
OL,7,Fright that IPP sentences were
OL,8,Fabolished, and that it has already
OL,9,Ftaken action to support affected
OL,10,Foffenders to move on with their lives.
OL,12,FWhat are IPP sentences?
OL,14,FIPP sentences were created by the
OL,15,FCriminal Justice Act 2003, and were
OL,16,Fdesigned to protect the public from
OL,17,Fserious offenders considered
OL,18,F"dangerous" but whose crime did not
OL,19,Fmerit a life sentence.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/15
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,434,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1776280294
OL,3,C'It ruins you': the impact of being
OL,4,Cindefinitely imprisoned
OL,6,FThe sentences were indeterminate,
OL,7,Fmeaning that after serving a minimum
OL,8,Fterm in prison, offenders had to apply
OL,9,Fto the Parole Board for release.
OL,11,FIf the Parole Board believed the
OL,12,Fprisoner was still a risk to the
OL,13,Fpublic, the individual could be
OL,14,Fdetained indefinitely, and could not
OL,15,Freapply for another year.
OL,17,FEven if an offender was given parole,
OL,18,Fthey remained on supervised license
OL,19,Ffor at least ten years and could be
OL,20,Fdetained again if they breached their
OL,21,Flicense conditions.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/15
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,434,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1776280294
OL,3,C'It ruins you': the impact of being
OL,4,Cindefinitely imprisoned
OL,6,FIPP sentences were abolished in 2012,
OL,7,Fwith the acknowledgment that they were
OL,8,Fused inconsistently and more broadly
OL,9,Fthan anticipated.
OL,11,FIn 2014, a European Court of Human
OL,12,FRights case found that the sentences
OL,13,Fbreached human rights by failing to
OL,14,Fprovide prisoners with a reasonable
OL,15,Fopportunity to reduce their risk and
OL,16,Fsecure release.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/15
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,434,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1776280294
OL,3,C'It ruins you': the impact of being
OL,4,Cindefinitely imprisoned
OL,6,FAlthough the IPP prison population has
OL,7,Freduced by more than 50% since the
OL,8,Fsentences were abolished, thousands
OL,9,Fremain incarcerated years beyond their
OL,10,Fminimum term, waiting for the Parole
OL,11,FBoard to recommend their release.
OL,13,FThe impact of IPP sentences
OL,15,FHere in the West Country, there are 90
OL,16,Fprisoners still being held on IPP
OL,17,Fsentences, according to latest
OL,18,FMinistry of Justice figures.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/15
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,434,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1776280294
OL,3,C'It ruins you': the impact of being
OL,4,Cindefinitely imprisoned
OL,6,FCharities and organisations supporting
OL,7,Fprisoners say IPPs have led to severe
OL,8,Fmental health problems. According to
OL,9,Fcampaign group UNGRIPP, 96 prisoners
OL,10,Fserving indefinite sentences have
OL,11,Fcommitted suicide.
OL,13,FFormer inmate Ben was told he would
OL,14,Fserve a minimum of 2 years but ended
OL,15,Fup in prison for 14. He described IPP
OL,16,Fsentences as "degrading", leaving
OL,17,Fprisoners with no hope of release or
OL,18,Frehabilitation.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/15
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,434,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1776280294
OL,3,C'It ruins you': the impact of being
OL,4,Cindefinitely imprisoned
OL,6,FBen told ITV West Country: "It has had
OL,7,Fa massive effect. Coming out with
OL,8,Fmental health problems - personality
OL,9,Fdisorder, voices in my head, violent
OL,10,Ftendencies. I'm on a lot of anti-
OL,11,Fpsychotic medication. Before I went to
OL,12,Fprison, yeah I had a drink and drug
OL,13,Fproblem, but I wasn't mentally ill."
OL,15,FHe said: "People in the pub can turn
OL,16,Faround and say you deserved it. Yeah,
OL,17,Ffine, I deserved to be punished, but
OL,18,Fdon't send me to prison for a sentence
OL,19,Fthat warrants four years, and I end up
OL,20,Fdoing 14 years.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/15
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,434,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43309
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1776280294
OL,3,C'It ruins you': the impact of being
OL,4,Cindefinitely imprisoned
OL,6,F"There is no justification in it. It
OL,7,Fruins you. It has ruined me."
OL,9,FBen concluded: "It takes everything
OL,10,Faway from you, it takes your dignity,
OL,11,Fyour self-pride, your self-worth,
OL,12,Fthat's what it does to a person."
OL,14,FRoddy Russell from Gloucestershire was
OL,15,Fat the protest in Westminster. His
OL,16,Fbrother was imprisoned in 2009 with a
OL,17,Ftwo-and-a-half-year minimum tariff,
OL,18,Fand has not yet been released.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/15
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,434,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43310
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1776280294
OL,3,C'It ruins you': the impact of being
OL,4,Cindefinitely imprisoned
OL,6,FHe said: "The retrospective element of
OL,7,Fit should have been abolished by the
OL,8,FMinistry of Justice years ago.
OL,10,F"I'm really disappointed with the
OL,11,FMinistry of Justice and the ministers
OL,12,Fthat have the authority to end this
OL,13,Ftragic, awful and disgraceful
OL,14,Finjustice."
OL,16,FThe Ministry of Justice
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/15
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
